      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative Hemolysis Index Comparison — CFD vs. Blood Analogue Data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values were compared against hemolysis measurements collected from a prospective observational registry of patients undergoing CPB with the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. Across all five flow-speed operating points, CFD RH predictions fell within the uncertainty bounds of the registry data, with RH < 1 confirmed at worst-case conditions. The observational dataset spans 47 clinical cases over 18 months, providing a physiologically representative population. Agreement metrics include mean absolute error of 0.04 RH units and a 95% prediction interval that fully encompasses the clinical observations. The breadth of the clinical cohort and the consistency of the haematological assays employed lend high confidence to the comparison, supporting the conclusion that the CFD model adequately captures hemolysis trends relevant to the COU.",
      "quantitativeMetric": "Mean absolute error 0.04 RH units; 95% PI coverage 100%",
      "validationStatus": "passed",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/cpb-registry-study",
        "type": "Activity",
        "name": "CPB Clinical Registry Hemolysis Study",
